      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand this might be really worrying, but it's important not to make any changes to your insulin dosage without consulting with your healthcare provider. The symptoms you're describing could be related to exercise-induced hypoglycemia. However, they could also be due to other factors. Ideally, check your blood sugar level to see where your level stands, and have a snack or juice with some carbohydrates if your level is low. Remember to always consult your healthcare provider before making any changes to your diabetes management plan.",
