      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable that you're feeling anxious and want to address your symptoms, but it's crucial to follow the advice of your healthcare provider for safely managing your insulin doses during exercise. Self-adjusting your insulin levels without professional guidance can be dangerous. When you have symptoms that concern you, it's always safest to check your blood sugar with a glucometer and call your healthcare team for their input. They can help you interpret the results and decide on the best course of action. Remember, safety is the priority, and your healthcare team is there to assist you in managing your diabetes effectively. For future long runs or intense workouts, also ensure to have a pre-exercise meal or snack to prevent hypoglycemia. It can be beneficial to create an exercise plan with your healthcare provider that accounts for activity changes.",
